Anthocarp sessile or subsessile, clavate, narrowly oblanceoloid or subellipsoid, to 4 x 1.5 mm, obtuse, green, 4-5-ribbed, 
					ribs stipitate-glandular, viscous, groove between ribs smooth, with numerous linear, white raphides appearing as minute streaks; 
					seed narrowly ovoid, ca. 2 mm, castaneous.

Leaves alternate; 
					petiolate; 
					blade broad, entire.

Woody vine, armed, high-climbing, or tree to 20 m; 
