Petiole 1-12 mm long; 
					blade often seemingly with salt-exuding hydathode glands above, oblong, elliptical, narrowly oblanceolate, linear-oblong or linear, 1-5(-7) x 0.2-2.5 cm, 
						apex obtuse to acute, 
						base clasping and often overlapping; 
					
					venation indistinct.

Flowers solitary,  on a glabrous pedicel to 2 cm long; 
					perianth-tube obconic to subcampanulate, 1.5-3 mm long, 
						lobes lanceolate, ovate-lanceolate or ovate, 4-10 x 2-6 mm, thickened,  outside usually prominently veined and green,  appendage 1-2 mm long, inside pink, lilac or pinkish-purple, 
						margin scarious pink or hyaline; 
					
